USE REF HOOKS
------------------

STEP 1 : import the useRef hook

STEP 2 : create one useRef state

        const emailRef = useRef()

STEP 3: Create one jsx element. and apply ref attribute value in useRef state.

STEP 4 : After assign that ref attribute you can cotrol the elements.


STEP 5 : you have to change modify the elements color, bg color, focus etc,



Example
---------
import {useRef} from 'react'

function LoginPage(){

    const emailRef = useRef()

    useEffect(()=>{
        
        emailRef.current.focus()
        emailRef.current.style.color = 'red'
        emailRef.current.style.backgroundColor = 'blue'
        emailRef.current.value = "saravanan.mca1992@tcs.com


    },[])

    return <div >
       
                  <input type = "text"
                         name = 'email' 

                         ref = {emailRef} />
                          
    </div>
}


export default LoginPage
